name: Olympics
summary: The closing ceremony of the Paris Olympics featured performances from Billie Eilish, Snoop Dogg, and the Red Hot Chili Peppers. Tom Cruise also made an appearance, and the ceremony included a handover to Los Angeles, which will host the next Olympics in 2028. The event was full of music and stunts, and included a special performance by H.E.R. The closing ceremony marked the end of the Paris Olympics, but also raised questions about the upcoming Olympics in Los Angeles. One article suggested that it may be difficult for Los Angeles to replicate the success of Paris, while another article focused on the sibling rivalry between two kayakers in the Olympics. Meanwhile, one writer took the opportunity to go swimming in the Seine River, while another celebrated the victory of Team USA's basketball team.

name: Jordan Chiles
summary: The Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) has ruled that Romanian gymnast Catalina Ponor should be awarded the bronze medal in the women's floor exercise at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics in place of American gymnast Jordan Chiles. The decision was made after CAS found that the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG) had incorrectly awarded the bronze to Chiles due to a scoring error. Chiles must now return her bronze medal and will no longer be eligible to receive any prize money or other benefits associated with the medal. The US is appealing the decision to the Swiss Federal Tribunal.
